Pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid.

Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn
the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and
leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue
to cook in its own steam).

While the rice cooks, cut the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%g} into thirds.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a #measuring jug{}, combine the @Ketjap Manis{50%g}, @Rice Vinegar{30%ml} and
@Cornflour{10%g}. Mix well until smooth.

Once smooth, stir in the @Tomato Ketchup{2%tbsp}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water for the Sauce{150%ml}.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix until combined. Set your stir-fry sauce aside for now.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #large frying pan{} on low heat.

Once hot, add the @Chicken Gyozas{1%pack} and fry until golden, ~{3%mins}.

Add 4 tbsp of @water{4%tbsp} to the pan and cover with a #lid (or #foil{}). Cook until piping hot,
~{3%mins} more.

Transfer to a #bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

Wipe out the (now empty) pan and pop it back on medium heat with a generous drizzle of
@oil{drizzle}.

Once hot, add the Tenderstem® and @Sliced Mushrooms{80%g}. Stir-fry for ~{7-8%mins} until
the veg is tender.

Next, add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{30%secs}.

Add your stir-fry sauce to the pan and simmer, continuously stirring, until the sauce has
just thickened, ~{1%min}.

Remove from the heat. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash
more @water{splash} if the sauce needs loosening a little.

Gently stir your gyozas through the sauce until coated.

Share the rice out between your #bowls{}.

Gently spoon over the stir-fried veg and gyozas. Drizzle over any remaining sauce from the pan.

Enjoy!